    "description": "Tsunami-HySEA is a software package designed for simulating tsunami propagation and inundation using the shallow water equations. It employs advanced numerical methods to accurately model the behavior of tsunamis, making it a valuable tool for researchers and emergency planners in understanding and mitigating the impacts of these natural disasters. The software is developed by the EDANYA Research Group at the University of Málaga and is available under the GNU General Public License v2.0.",

